		CEO Spotlight
	
Inside the Success of Ilene Gordon, Ingredion CEO
How she transformed the former Corn Products into a leader in specialty food ingredients. 


 







By

Reshma Kapadia

 Biography




 




May 29, 2015 8:53 p.m. ET


Ilene Gordon has always been a woman with a plan. As a teenager, the chief executive of Ingredion, a leading processor of starches, sweeteners, and specialty food ingredients, knew her summer plans by January. Based on advice from a mentor in business school, she planned to give birth to her first child at least five years into her career. And, by age 30, she had mapped out a career path that would get her to the top of a big company. Gordon, 61, can safely say much has worked out as she planned. After graduating from the...
	      




 


